    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> with the <strong>chopped parsley</strong>, <strong>lemon zest</strong>, <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>– these are your <strong>lemon breadcrumbs</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>cod fillet[s] </strong>to a separate <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) and top with the<strong> lemon breadcrumbs</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 13-15 min or until cooked through – this is your <strong>lemon crusted cod</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 6,
